{"lemma":"رَأْيِ","slug":"رَأْيِ","root":"ر.#.#","root_slug":"ر-_-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-_-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رَأْيِ","root":"رأي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14324","n14333","n17199"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A3%D9%92%D9%8A%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to see (to perceive with the eyes)","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"لَا أَرَى شَيْئًا.","english":"I can't see anything."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to see again in one's mind, to play back a memory, to look back on"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to deem true, to opine or hold the opinion of, to have that outlook on something, to see or view it that way, to be of that thinking or to have such thoughts","examples":[{"text":"فَلَمَّا بَلَغَ مَعَهُ ٱلسَّعۡىَ قَالَ يَـٰـبُنَىَّ إِنِّىٓ أَرَىٰ فِى ٱلۡمَنَامِ أَنِّىٓ أَذۡبَحُكَ فَٱنۡظُرۡ مَاذَا تَرَىٰ قَالَ يَـٰٓـأَبَتِ ٱفۡعَلۡ مَا تُؤۡمَرُ سَتَجِدُنِىٓ إِن شَاءَ ٱللهُ مِنَ ٱلصَّابِرِينَ","english":"\"Then when the boy reached the age to work with him, Abraham said, “O my dear son! I have seen in a dream that I ˹must˺ sacrifice you. So tell me what you think.” He replied, “O my dear father! Do as you are commanded. Allah willing, you will find me steadfast.”\""}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to review in one's mind, to consider it, to reflect on it, to contemplate, to review something to see its deeper significance, to look back over, to speculate upon"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to plant a flag or banner in the ground, to place down one's ensign or mark"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hit someone's lung, to complain of pain in one's lungs","tags":["obsolete","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dream, to have a dream","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to imagine, to fancy, to conceive a thought or to conceptualize, to see (to perceive in one's dream)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to envision, to foresee, to suppose, to anticipate a future outcome, to speculate or reckon it will be, to have a premonition or forewarning"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Biblical Hebrew רָאָה (rāʾâ) and Ge'ez ርእየ (rəʾyä)."},"ipa":["/ra.ʔaː/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14324","headword_ar":"رَاَى","root":"rA^Y","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, &c.,) for which some say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA","text_ar":"رَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[suppressing the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (M,) and some say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA='a","text_ar":"رَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bwA^","text_ar":"بوا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and M and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ryA^","text_ar":"ريا"},{"kind":"text","text":",) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAfa","text_ar":"خَافَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA in the latter art.,) formed by transposition, (T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bwA^","text_ar":"بوا"},{"kind":"text","text":",) first pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K, &c.,) for which some say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rayotu","text_ar":"رَيْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M,) but the former is that which is general and preferred, (T, M,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaraY","text_ar":"يَرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M,) for which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaroA^aY","text_ar":"يَرْاَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with the root, is said by none except [the tribe of] Teym-erRibáb, (T, M,) or by such as require this form in poetry, (S,) sec. pers. fem. sing. and pl., alike,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarayona","text_ar":"تَرَيْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", so that you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarayonaniY","text_ar":"تَرَيْنَنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[with an affixed pronoun], and if you will you may say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarayon~iY","text_ar":"تَرَيْنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", incorporating one"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"into the other by teshdeed, (S,) imperative"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ra","text_ar":"رَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iro'a","text_ar":"اـِرْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, T, S, M,) the people of El-Hijáz saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ra","text_ar":"رَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"dual"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rayaA","text_ar":"رَيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. masc."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawoA","text_ar":"رَوْا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rayona","text_ar":"رَيْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and Teym saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Airo'a","text_ar":"اِرْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., (T, M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruw^oyapN","text_ar":"رُوْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riy~apN","text_ar":"رِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, K,) the former being altered to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwoyapN","text_ar":"رُوْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and then to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruy~apN","text_ar":"رُيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and then to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riy~apN","text_ar":"رِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^oYN","text_ar":"رَاْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA='apN","text_ar":"رَا=ءَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K, [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ap","text_ar":"رَاَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAEapN","text_ar":"رَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in measure], (S,) in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not necessarily a restrictive to unity, (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAyapN","text_ar":"رَايَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K [but this I do not find elsewhere]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riy^oyaAnN","text_ar":"رِيْيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, M, TA,) for which last we find in the copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruw^oyaAn","text_ar":"رُوْيَان"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He saw"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a person or thing]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) in this sense the verb has [only] one objective complement: (S, Msb:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotuhu","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AistaroA^ayotuhu","text_ar":"اِستَرْاَيْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, K,) for which some say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisotarayotuhu","text_ar":"اِسْتَرَيْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirotaA^ayotuhu","text_ar":"اِرْتَاَيْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, K,) for which some say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Airotayotuhu","text_ar":"اِرْتَيْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M,) all signifying the same, (T, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a person and a thing, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the eye;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, Msb, K, TA;) [or so,] and also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the mind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M and K in relation to the first, and K in relation to all.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruw^oyapN","text_ar":"رُوْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of several sorts: (TA:) first, it signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeing with the eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with what serves for the same purpose as the organ of sight;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying in the Kur [ix. 106],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waquli A@EomaluwA fasayaraYA@ll~`hu Eamalakumo","text_ar":"وَقُلِ ا@عْمَلُوا فَسَيَرَىا@للّٰهُ عَمَلَكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And Say thou, Work ye, for God will see your work"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because the sense of sight cannot be attributed to God: (TA:) [and similar to this is the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^aY fiyhi ka*aA","text_ar":"رَاَى فِيهِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He saw in him such a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^aY minohu ka*aA","text_ar":"رَاَى مِنْهُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He experienced from him such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"] Secondly, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeing by supposition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fancy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araY A^an~a","text_ar":"اَرَى اَنَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodFA munoTaliqN","text_ar":"زَيْدًا مُنْطَلِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I suppose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fancy, that Zeyd is going away"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) Thirdly, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeing by reflection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consideration;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying [in the Kur viii. 50],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~iY A^araY maA laA tarawona","text_ar":"اـِنِّى اَرَى مَا لَا تَرَوْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily I see by reflection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consideration, what ye see not"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) Fourthly, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeing with the mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mentally;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"judging,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing; a sense in which the inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^oYN","text_ar":"رَاْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is more commonly used;] (M, * K, * TA;) as in the saying in the Kur [liii. 11],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA ka*aba Alfuw^aAdu maA raA^aY","text_ar":"مَا كَذَبَ الفُوَادُ مَا رَاَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The heart did not belie what he mentally saw"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [Of these meanings, other exs. here follow; with exs. of similar meanings.] ―         -b2-  An ex. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA","text_ar":"رَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^aY","text_ar":"رَاَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in the saying of a poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"mano raA mivola maEodaAna boni aHoyaY"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Who has seen the like of Maadán the son of Yahyà?"},{"kind":"text","text":"the measure being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAfir","text_ar":"وَافِر"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the first foot reduced to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufoEalotuno","text_ar":"مُفْعَلْتُنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHamodulil~`hi EalaY","text_ar":"الحَمْدُلِلّٰهِ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riy~atiki","text_ar":"رِيَّتِكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruw^oyatika","text_ar":"رُوْيَتِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", altered in the manner explained above, [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Praise be to God for the seeing of thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (M, K, *) is a saying mentioned by IAar. (M.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuwmuwA liruw^oyatihi","text_ar":"صُومُوا لِرُوْيَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fast ye"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the"},{"kind":"text","text":"time of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeing it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[referring to the new moon of Ramadán;] i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when ye see it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) In the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotuhu qaAy^imFA","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُهُ قَايِمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw him standing"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qAy^mA","text_ar":"قايما"},{"kind":"text","text":"is in the accus. case as a denotative of state. (Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^oYu EayoniY zayodFA faEala *aAka","text_ar":"رَاْىُ عَيْنِى زَيْدًا فَعَلَ ذَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My eye saw"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my eye's seeing"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd do that"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is held by Sb to be an instance of an anomalous use of an inf. n., and is [said to be] the only instance of the kind, among inf. ns. of trans. verbs except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEu A^u*uniY","text_ar":"سَمْعُ اُذُنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA: but in a copy of the former written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^oYa EynY","text_ar":"رَاْىَ عينى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEaA*nY","text_ar":"سَمْعَاذنى"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotuhu raA^oYa AlEayoni","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُهُ رَاْىَ العَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where the eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sight, fell upon him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEayonK m~aA A^arayan~aka","text_ar":"بِعَيْنٍ مَّا اَرَيَنَّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"With some eye I will assuredly see thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a saying mentioned by AZ as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hasten thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEojalo","text_ar":"اِعْجَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus in copies of the S and in the TA, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaj~ilo","text_ar":"عَجِّلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in one copy of the S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"work thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEomalo","text_ar":"اِعْمَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", thus in two copies of the S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and be as though I were looking at thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) it is said to one whom you send, and require to be quick; and means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pause not for anything, for it is as though I were looking at thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eyn","text_ar":"عين"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^aY AlmakaAnu","text_ar":"رَاَى المَكَانُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmakaAna","text_ar":"المَكَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The place faced"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or (as we say)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"looked upon"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the place, as though seeing it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA,) is tropical: (TA:) [and in like manner you say,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAriY taraY daArahu","text_ar":"دَارِى تَرَى دَارَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My house faces"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"looks upon"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his house."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, IAth, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^aYfiY manaAmihi ruw^oyaA","text_ar":"رَاَىفِى مَنَامِهِ رُوْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He saw,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fancied that he saw, in his sleep, a vision,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dream"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, Msb, K. *) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alamo tara A_ilaY","text_ar":"اَلَمْ تَرَ اـِلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Has thou not considered such a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"so as to be admonished thereby?] is a phrase used on an occasion of wonder (IAth, K, TA) at a thing, and in rousing the attention of the person to whom it is addressed; as in the saying in the Kur [ii. 244],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alamo tara A_ilaY A@l~a*iyna xarajuwA mino diyaArihimo","text_ar":"اَلَمْ تَرَ اـِلَى ا@لَّذِينَ خَرَجُوا مِنْ دِيَارِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hast thou not considered those who went forth from their houses,"},{"kind":"text","text":"so as to be admonished by their case?]; meaning, hast thou not wondered at their act, and has not their case come to thy knowledge? and so in other instances in the same: (IAth, TA:) Er-Rághib says that, when"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayot","text_ar":"رَاَيْت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is made trans. by means of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY","text_ar":"اـِلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", it denotes consideration that leads to the becoming admonished. (TA.) In like manner also, (IAth, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araA^ayotaka","text_ar":"اَرَاَيْتَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araA^ayotakumaA","text_ar":"اَرَاَيْتَكُمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araA^ayotakumo","text_ar":"اَرَاَيْتَكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, IAth, K,) and to a woman"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araA^ayotaki","text_ar":"اَرَاَيْتَكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and to a pl. number of women"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araA^ayotakun~a","text_ar":"اَرَاَيْتَكُنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,) [which may be lit. rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hast thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have ye two,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"considered?"},{"kind":"text","text":"] are expressions used to arouse attention, (IAth, TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tell thou me"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tell ye two me"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; (T, IAth, K;) as in the saying in the Kur [xvii. 64],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAla A^araA^ayotaka h`*aA A@l~a*iY kar~amotu EalaY~a","text_ar":"قَالَ اَرَاَيْتَكَ هٰذَا ا@لَّذِى كَرَّمْتُ عَلَىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"page_break","n":999},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"said, Hast thou considered?"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tell me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"respecting"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this whom Thou hast honoured above me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and in the same [vi. 40 and 47],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalo A^araA^ayotakumo","text_ar":"قَلْ اَرَاَيْتَكُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino A^ataAkumo Ea*aAbu A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"اـِنْ اَتَاكُمْ عَذَابُ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Say thou, Have ye considered?"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tell me, if the punishment of God come upon you"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and occurring without the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k","text_ar":"ك"},{"kind":"text","text":"in other places thereof: (IAth, TA:) you say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araA^ayota zayodFA","text_ar":"اَرَاَيْتَ زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araA^ayotaka zayodFA","text_ar":"اَرَاَيْتَكَ زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tell thou me"},{"kind":"text","text":"[respecting"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Mgh:) and for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araA^ayota","text_ar":"اَرَاَيْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araA^ayotaka","text_ar":"اَرَاَيْتَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.] some say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arayota","text_ar":"اَرَيْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arayotaka","text_ar":"اَرَيْتَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) the pronunciation without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the more common: the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araA^ayotaka","text_ar":"اَرَاَيْتَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. is always with fet-h; and accord. to the grammarians of accredited science, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k","text_ar":"ك"},{"kind":"text","text":"in these cases is redundant; (T;) [i. e.] it is a particle of allocution, to corroborate the pronoun ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":", which it therefore immediately follows in every case, distinguishing the genders and numbers by its own variations, which are the same as those of the pronominal affix of the second person]: (Bd in vi. 40:) [IHsh says,] the correct opinion is that of Sb; that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an agent, and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k","text_ar":"ك"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a particle of allocution: (Mughnee in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k","text_ar":"ك"},{"kind":"text","text":":) but sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araA^ayotaka","text_ar":"اَرَاَيْتَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. mean"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halo raA^ayota nafosaka","text_ar":"هَلْ رَاَيْتَ نَفْسَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k","text_ar":"ك"},{"kind":"text","text":"being in this case an objective complement [and the verb being differently rendered according as it has not, or has, a second objective complement, as is shown here by what precedes and what follows]. (T.) In"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aturaAka","text_ar":"اَتُرَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, [from ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uriYa","text_ar":"اُرِىَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", not from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruy^iYa","text_ar":"رُيِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AtZn~","text_ar":"اتظنّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataZun~u","text_ar":"اَتَظُنُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thinkest thou?"},{"kind":"text","text":"], the pronoun [as some term it, but properly the final particle,] is [a particle of allocution] like that in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araA^ayotaka","text_ar":"اَرَاَيْتَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur vi. 40 and 47 [cited above; and in the same sense as this latter phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aturaAka","text_ar":"اَتُرَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tell thou me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Har p. 570.) ―         -b5-  When"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^aY","text_ar":"رَاَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He knew,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he thought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) it has two objective complements: (S, Msb:) or when it has two objective complements, it necessarily means knowing [or the like]. (Er-Rághib, TA.) [In this case,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA=hu","text_ar":"رَا=هُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He saw,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knew, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, to be:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he thought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"judged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"held, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, to be;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he regarded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"held, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, as."},{"kind":"text","text":"] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu zayodFA EaAlimFA","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ زَيْدًا عَالِمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, *) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaliymFA","text_ar":"حَلِيمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I knew"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saw Zeyd to be learned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forbearing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, M, Msb;) as though seeing him to be so with the eye: (M:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I thought him"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be so."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) In like manner, also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraA='ayotuhu","text_ar":"تَرَا=ءَيْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I thought him to be."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 211.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yarawonahumo mivolayohimo raA^oYa A@lEayoni","text_ar":"يَرَوْنَهُمْ مِثْلَيْهِمْ رَاْىَ ا@لعَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [iii. 11], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They"},{"kind":"text","text":"[who were the unbelievers]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thinking them"},{"kind":"text","text":"[who were fighting in the cause of God]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twice as many as they, according to"},{"kind":"text","text":"the evidence of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sight of the eye."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) The pass. form of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^aY","text_ar":"رَاَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"has [only] one objective complement: you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruy^iYa zayodN EaAqilFA","text_ar":"رُيِىَ زَيْدٌ عَاقِلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd was thought"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be intelligent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aal~a*iY A^uraAhu","text_ar":"اَلَّذِى اُرَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the verb in the pass. form, means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*YAZn~","text_ar":"الذىاظنّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uZan~u","text_ar":"اُظَنُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He whom I am thought to be;"},{"kind":"text","text":"if from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruy^iYa","text_ar":"رُيِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*YA^aZun~u","text_ar":"الذىاَظُنُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what I think,"},{"kind":"text","text":"if from ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uriYa","text_ar":"اُرِىَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": it is often used in the latter sense]. (Msb.) ―         -b6-  You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^aY fiY AlA^amori raA^oyFA","text_ar":"رَاَى فِى الاَمْرِ رَاْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He formed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"held, an opinion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a persuasion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a belief, respecting the affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiYAlfiqohi","text_ar":"فِىالفِقْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the science of the law"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al~a*iY A^araAhu","text_ar":"الَّذِى اَرَاهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That to which I take,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which I hold, as my opinion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persuasion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belief."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yaraY raA^oYa Al$~uraApi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَرَى رَاْىَ الشُّرَاةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one holds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"believes, the tenets,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belief, of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$rAp","text_ar":"شراة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a certain sect of schismatics; pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aArK","text_ar":"شَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) When"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^aY","text_ar":"رَاَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [thus] used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He held,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"believed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"it has [only] one objective complement. (Msb.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tara maA","text_ar":"لَا تَرَ مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K, TA, [mentioned also in the K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trm","text_ar":"ترم"},{"kind":"text","text":", in which art. in the CK CK it is written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA taromA","text_ar":"لا تَرْما"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA taraY maA","text_ar":"لَا تَرَى مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawo tara maA","text_ar":"لَوْ تَرَ مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawo taraYmaA","text_ar":"لَوْ تَرَىمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, TA, [in copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awotara maA","text_ar":"اَوْتَرَ مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", which I think a mistranscription, and for which is put in the TA, as on the authority of IAar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A* tr mA","text_ar":"اذ تر ما"},{"kind":"text","text":", app. a mistranscription of a mistranscription, i. e. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AwtrmA","text_ar":"اوترما"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo tara maA","text_ar":"لَمْ تَرَ مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, K, TA,) in this last case with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tara","text_ar":"تَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[only, agreeably with a general rule], are forms of expression meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA siy~amaA","text_ar":"لَا سِيَّمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e., virtually,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Above all,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"especially"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T, K, TA:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laxabiyvN walaA tara maA fulaAnN","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَخَبِيثٌ وَلَا تَرَ مَا فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa laA taraY maA fulaAnN","text_ar":"وَ لَا تَرَى مَا فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa lawo tara maA fulaAnN","text_ar":"وَ لَوْ تَرَ مَا فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walawo taraY","text_ar":"وَلَوْ تَرَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA fulaAnN","text_ar":"مَا فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":".alamo tara maA fulaAnN","text_ar":".َلَمْ تَرَ مَا فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is bad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"base,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wicked; and above all,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"especially, such a one:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA tara maA fulaAnN","text_ar":"وَلَا تَرَ مَا فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA taraYmaA fulaAnN","text_ar":"وَلَا تَرَىمَا فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", properly meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA taraYmivola Al~a*iY huwa fulaAnN","text_ar":"وَلَا تَرَىمِثْلَ الَّذِى هُوَ فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and thou will not see the like of him who is such a one;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mivola","text_ar":"مِثْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa","text_ar":"هُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being understood: and in like manner are to be explained the other forms of expression here mentioned]: in all of these forms,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"flAn","text_ar":"فلان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is in the nom. case: all are mentioned by Lh, on the authority of Ks. (T, TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ato","text_ar":"رَاَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also said of a woman, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She saw what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aroy^iyap","text_ar":"التَّرْيِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~ariy~ap","text_ar":"التَّرِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a little yellowness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whiteness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blood on the occasion of menstruation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotuhu","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[form"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~iy^apu","text_ar":"الرِّيَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I hit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hurt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K, *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"struck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smote,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riy^ap","text_ar":"رِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lungs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, M, Msb, K, Er-Rághib:) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"warayotuhu","text_ar":"وَرَيْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruy^iYa","text_ar":"رُيِىَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had a complaint of his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riy^ap","text_ar":"رِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lungs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroA^aY","text_ar":"اَرْاَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu raAyapF","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ رَايَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I stuck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fixed, a banner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"standard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rY","text_ar":"رى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and K in the present art.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into the ground;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araA^ayotuhaA","text_ar":"اَرَاَيْتُهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, K,) as some say: (T:) the latter is mentioned by Lh; but [ISd says,] I hold that it is anomalous, and is properly only"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arayayotuhaA","text_ar":"اَرَيَيْتُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rY","text_ar":"رى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^aYAlz~anodu","text_ar":"رَاَىالزَّنْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waraY","text_ar":"وَرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wariYa","text_ar":"وَرِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"znd","text_ar":"زند"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of wood for producing fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became kindled."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, M, K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu Alz~anoda","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ الزَّنْدَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I kindled the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"znd","text_ar":"زند"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","T","S","AZ","Msb","K","Lh","TA","IAth","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n14333","headword_ar":"رَاْىٌ","root":"rA^Y","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^aY","text_ar":"رَاَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (T, S, K:) [and is also a subst.: used as a subst.,] it means The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^oY","text_ar":"رَاْى"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the eye; (Lth, T, Msb;) i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sight"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruw^oyapN","text_ar":"رُوْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.: (Msb:) and also, of the mind; (Lth, T;) [i. e.,] it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mental perception:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conception: idea: nation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belief;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) as a subst., not as inf. n.: (M:)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1001},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"judgment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persuasion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opinion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a preponderating belief of one of two things that are inconsistent, each with the other:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that a man has seen with his mind, looked into, examined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"considered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A@rotaA=hu","text_ar":"مَا ا@رْتَا=هُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and believed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tenet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forecast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skill in affairs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) [and hence it often means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"counsel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"advice:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroA='N","text_ar":"اَرْا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=raA='N","text_ar":"ا=رَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) the latter formed by transposition, [being for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aA^oraA='N","text_ar":"اَاْرَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroY'K","text_ar":"اَرْىءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arow^uYN","text_ar":"اَرْوُىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZobK","text_ar":"اَظْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZobuYN","text_ar":"اَظْبُىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (Lh, M, K, TA, in some copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroYN","text_ar":"اَرْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruy^iY~N","text_ar":"رُيِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riy^iY~N","text_ar":"رِيِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[both originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruw^uwYN","text_ar":"رُوُوىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Lh, M, TA,) in the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruY~N","text_ar":"رُىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm, [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raY~N","text_ar":"رَىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riY~N","text_ar":"رِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, (TA,) and [quasipl. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ray^iY~N","text_ar":"رَيِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Day^iynN","text_ar":"ضَيِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAA^aDal~a raA^oyahu","text_ar":"مَااَضَلَّ رَاْيَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How erroneous is his mental perception,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.!], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAA^aDal~a","text_ar":"مَااَضَلَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aruA=hu","text_ar":"اَرُا=هُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How erroneous are his mental perceptions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.!]. (Lth, T.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSoHaAbu Alr~aA^oYi","text_ar":"اَصْحَابُ الرَّاْىِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [often meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The speculatists,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"theorists,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as used by those who treat of the traditions, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the followers of analogy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because they pronounce according to their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^oY","text_ar":"رَاْى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or belief, &c.,] in relation to that concerning which they have not found any [tradition such as is termed]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hadiyv","text_ar":"حَدِيث"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avar","text_ar":"اَثَر"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAth, K, TA,) or in relation to that which is dubious to them in a tradition. (IAth, TA.) But accord. to the usage of others, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN mino A^ahuli Alr~aA^oY","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مِنْ اَهُلِ الرَّاْى"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one holds the belief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opinion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heretics,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"schismatics, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xawaArij","text_ar":"خَوَارِج"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and says according to their persuasion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Sometimes, also, this phrase means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is of the people of intelligence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of counsel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"advice."},{"kind":"text","text":"] See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ray^iY~N","text_ar":"رَيِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN *uw raA^oYK","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ ذُو رَاْىٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man having mental perception,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skill in affairs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  See also the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":["T","S","K","Msb","M","Mgh","Lh","TA","IAth"]},{"entry_id":"n17199","headword_ar":"رَاىٌ","root":"rY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}